title: Snippet gate fixture — Z2 gated markers end-to-end
story: snippet-gate
description: A gated {key} marker renders through the full platform stack. The `note` fragment rides the mentions gate (the brass bell is here — presence in the marker's room), the `hum` fragment rides the ADR-211 registered gate seam (the machine is humming — a state condition). Both start gated out; the description must render clean with no stray separators.
---

# Both fragments gated out: clean prose, no separators leak.
> look
[OK: contains "Shelves line the walls. A door leads north."]
[OK: not contains "brass bell gleams"]
[OK: not contains "vibrates"]

# Flip the seam-gated condition: the machine starts humming.
> examine machine
[OK: contains "shudders into a low hum"]

# The hum fragment now splices at its clause site (platform comma).
> look
[OK: contains "walls, and the air vibrates faintly."]
[OK: not contains "brass bell gleams"]

# Fetch the bell — presence (mentions) gates the note fragment in.
> north
[OK: contains "cramped annex"]

> take bell
[OK: contains "Taken"]

> south
[OK: contains "Lab"]

# Both fragments now render, in marker order, each with its own comma join.
> look
[OK: contains "walls, and a brass bell gleams on a shelf, and the air vibrates faintly."]

# Drop the bell in the annex again: the note fragment gates back out.
> north
[OK: contains "Annex"]

> drop bell
[OK: contains "Dropped"]

> south
[OK: contains "Lab"]

> look
[OK: contains "walls, and the air vibrates faintly."]
[OK: not contains "brass bell gleams"]
